-- Mechel Chairman Zyuzin Complains to Medvedev About Tax Probes
-- B y   I l y a   K h r e n n i k o v
-- 2012-08-06T23:54:58Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-08-06/mechel-chairman-zyuzin-complains-to-medvedev-about-tax-probes.html
OAO Mechel’s chairman, Russian
billionaire Igor Zyuzin, complained to Prime Minister  Dmitry
Medvedev  about an investigation into the coal producer’s taxes,
he said in remarks broadcast on state television Rossiya 24.  Tax and antitrust authorities are looking into Mechel’s
practice of charging domestic and foreign companies different
prices, said Zyuzin, the company’s chairman and main owner.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ilya Khrennikov in Moscow at 
 ikhrennikov@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
